items.title: GitHub's Agent HQ aims to solve enterprises' biggest AI coding problem: Too many agents, no central control
items.summary: Microsoft-owned developer platform announced Agent HQ at its Universe 2025 conference . The new architecture transforms GitHub into a unified control plane for managing multiple AI coding agents from competitors including Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, Cognition and xAI . The announcement marks what GitHub calls the transition from .quot;wave one, to .wave two, of AI-assisted development .

items.title: Intuit learned to build AI agents for finance the hard way: Trust lost in buckets, earned back in spoonfuls
items.summary: Intuit has announced Intuit Intelligence, a system that orchestrates specialized AI agents across its QuickBooks platform to handle tasks including sales tax compliance and payroll processing . The new development follow years of investment and improvement in Intuit's . Intuit's approach treats AI as a translation and orchestration, not a content generator .

items.summary: MiniMax-M2 is the latest open source large language model from Chinese startup of the same name . The model is available under a permissive, enterprise-friendly MIT License, meaning it is made available freely for developers to take, deploy, retrain, and use how they see fit . items.title: Anthropic rolls out Claude AI for finance, integrates with Excel to rival Microsoft Copilot
items.summary: San Francisco-based AI startup Anthropic is making its most aggressive push yet into the trillion-dollar financial services industry . Anthropic embeds its Claude AI assistant directly into Excel, connecting it to real-time market data . The move marks a significant escalation in Anthropic's campaign to position itself as the AI platform of choice for banks and asset managers .
